node.text:
London-based designer James Whitaker has created one of the coolest looking houses in Joshua Tree, California. The house is made from real shipping containers and includes all of your standard amenities including a living room, en-suites, a kitchen, and bathrooms. 

Follow @yup.that.exists

May be an image of ‎2 people and ‎text that says '‎Hadaka Matsuri is a 500-year-old festival in Japan that's nicknamed the "Naked Festival" Participants wear nothing but a cloth over their private parts and scramble to obtain lucky objects thrown into the crowd by local priests. The festival takes place every winter, and if you catch one of the objects you're said to have good luck throughout the year. Mک @yup.that.exists‎'‎‎.

node.text:
This years festival is on February 19th, 2022. Which is my birthday! It's a sign! 

Follow @yup.that.exists

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Yup That Exists on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'This beauty salon in Dubai has started giving microchip manicures. node.text:

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Yup That Exists on July 11, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'A science teacher at Oregon State University has discovered a brand new shade of blue while creating electronics materials. Mas Subramanian named the color "YlnMn Blue" after the yttrium, indium, and manganese in it. The new pigment is the first blue to be discovered in over 200 years. @yup.that.exists'.

Photo by Yup That Exists on July 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and text that says 'In 2014, seventh grader Shubham Banerjee created a braille printer out of LEGO blocks. After learning that low-income families couldn't afford braille printers that cost upwards of $2,000 he built one himself from a LEGO robotics kit. He released the instructions and software for free bringing the cost (for the parts) down to $350. ਨ- BONI @yup.that.exists'.

Photo by Yup That Exists on July 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'This mysterious pyramid in Argentina has been slowly growing naturally since the early 20th century. Its surrounding elements have been pulled towards it over time to be almost 500 feet tall. Scientists think its mystery is due to a small volcano located directly underneath the pyramid, but no one has yet to 100% prove its origin or how it got there. @yup.that.exists'.

Photo by Yup That Exists on July 08, 2021. May be art of 2 people and text that says 'KFC held a secret contest on their twitter. After only following 11 people (the 5 Spice Girls and 6 guys named herb) Mike Edgette pointed out it was because of their "secret blend" of 11 herbs and spices. He won a custom painting of himself piggybacking on the Colenol while holding a drumstick. @ yup that.exists'.
